TASK_DESCRIPTION=New async hook stop-recovery.sh: classify error type (transient API failure vs permanent missing-file vs config vs timeout), auto-respawn + redispatch for transient errors (max 1 retry), immediate escalation for permanent errors. Log all attempts via task_add_recovery_event(). Modify stop-notify.sh to check recovery before escalating. Depends on state machine (task 1). Research material: .doey/tasks/attachments/task-490-findings.md Area 4.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W3.1: Research stop hook chain, stop-respawn.sh, stop-notify.sh, common.sh transition_state(), and doey-task-helpers.sh task_add_recovery_event() to produce implementation spec:done\n2:W3.1: Create .claude/hooks/stop-recovery.sh with error classification and retry logic:done\n3:W3.2: Register stop-recovery.sh in settings.json and verify integration with stop-notify.sh:done
